claim.claim-text:
1. An implantable system, comprising:
communication circuitry configured to communicate with an implantable cardiac stimulator configured to sense activity and to receive signal indicative of the sensed activity;
a baroreflex stimulator configured to deliver a baroreflex stimulation therapy;
a controller operably connected to the communication circuitry and the baroreflex stimulator, the controller configured to:
automatically classify the sensed activity as an activity level selected from at least two preprogrammed activities levels; and
automatically select a baroreflex stimulation level for the baroreflex stimulation therapy based on the activity level of the detected activity, wherein the baroreflex stimulation level is selected from at least two preprogrammed stimulation levels.

14. An implantable system, comprising:
communication circuitry configured to communicate with an implantable cardiac stimulator configured to sense activity and to receive signal indicative of the sensed activity, wherein the sensed activity includes a signal indicative of sensed heart rate, sensed respiration or sensed acceleration;
a baroreflex stimulator configured to deliver a baroreflex stimulation therapy;
a controller operably connected to the communication circuitry and the baroreflex stimulator, the controller configured to:
automatically classify the sensed activity as an activity level selected from at least two preprogrammed activities levels, wherein automatically classifying the detected activity includes automatically classifying the detected activity as rest or exercise; and
automatically select a baroreflex stimulation level for the baroreflex stimulation therapy to apply baroreflex stimulation during rest and withdraw baroreflex stimulation during exercise.
